    dc:creator "Law, Chris J." ;
    dc:date "2018" ;
    dc:title "Mustela sibirica (Carnivora: Mustelidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573579>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573581>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573583> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573579>
    dc:description "Fig. 1.—Adult Mustela sibirica from Longleat Safari Park, Britain. Used with permission from photographer Clare Bambers." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573579/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573581>
    dc:description "Fig. 2.—Dorsal, ventral, and lateral views of cranium and lateral view of mandible of an adult female Mustela sibirica. Photograph taken at the California Academy of Sciences (CAS-MAM 11668). Total skull length is 5.3 cm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573581/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573583>
    dc:description "Fig. 3.—Geographic distribution of Mustela sibirica. Map redrawn from Abramov et al. (2016). Subspecies are: 1) M. s. sibirica; 2) M. s. charbinensis and M. s. manchurica; 3) M. s. coreana; 4) M. s. fontanierii; 5) M. s. quelpartis; 6) M. s. davidiana; 7) M. s. taivana; 8) M. s. moupinensis; 9) M. s. canigula; 10) M. s. subhemachalana; and 11) M. s. hodgsoni. 12) Indicates invasive populations." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573583/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

